div.p:
The practitioner who carved this verse at Stone Buddha Valley must have been familiar with the past-life story of selling one’s flesh for the sake of the Dharma, and possessed the same resolve in vowing to become a Buddha. Elsewhere, there are also practitioners who carved this verse into stone to show their resolve:
HSY 1 at Yellow Stone Cliff (Huangshiya 黄石崖) in Licheng 歷城, Jinan 濟南, around 526;
The Middle Cave of Xiao Nanhai 小南海 in Anyang 安陽, between 555 and 560.For an analysis of the inscription content and further references, see 544–547.
